.TH "snd_ctl_make_virtual_master" 9 "snd_ctl_make_virtual_master" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ctl_make_virtual_master \- Create a virtual master control
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct snd_kcontrol *" snd_ctl_make_virtual_master
.BI "(char *name "  ","
.BI "const unsigned int *tlv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
name string of the control element to create
.IP "tlv" 12
optional TLV int array for dB information
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates a virtual master control with the given name string.

After creating a vmaster element, you can add the follower controls
via \fBsnd_ctl_add_follower\fP or \fBsnd_ctl_add_follower_uncached\fP.

The optional argument \fItlv\fP can be used to specify the TLV information
for dB scale of the master control.  It should be a single element
with #SNDRV_CTL_TLVT_DB_SCALE, #SNDRV_CTL_TLV_DB_MINMAX or
#SNDRV_CTL_TLVT_DB_MINMAX_MUTE type, and should be the max 0dB.
.SH "RETURN"
The created control element, or NULL for errors (ENOMEM).
